# Data Model Schema

## Core Entities

### Company
- id: UUID (PK)
- name: string
- created_at: timestamp
- updated_at: timestamp

### Site
- id: UUID (PK)
- company_id: UUID (FK -> Company)
- name: string
- location: string
- created_at: timestamp
- updated_at: timestamp

### ValueStream
- id: UUID (PK)
- site_id: UUID (FK -> Site)
- name: string
- description: string
- target_efficiency: float
- created_at: timestamp
- updated_at: timestamp

### Cell
- id: UUID (PK)
- value_stream_id: UUID (FK -> ValueStream)
- name: string
- description: string
- status: enum(active, inactive, maintenance)
- target_cycle_time: integer
- created_at: timestamp
- updated_at: timestamp

### Operator
- id: UUID (PK)
- user_id: string (FK -> Clerk User)
- cell_id: UUID (FK -> Cell)
- name: string
- role: enum(operator, supervisor, admin)
- shift: enum(morning, afternoon, night)
- created_at: timestamp
- updated_at: timestamp

### ProductionCycle
- id: UUID (PK)
- cell_id: UUID (FK -> Cell)
- operator_id: UUID (FK -> Operator)
- start_time: timestamp
- end_time: timestamp
- actual_cycle_time: integer
- efficiency: float
- status: enum(completed, interrupted, error)
- notes: string
- created_at: timestamp

### Downtime
- id: UUID (PK)
- cell_id: UUID (FK -> Cell)
- operator_id: UUID (FK -> Operator)
- start_time: timestamp
- end_time: timestamp
- reason: enum(maintenance, setup, breakdown, material_shortage)
- description: string
- created_at: timestamp

### EfficiencyMetric
- id: UUID (PK)
- entity_type: enum(cell, value_stream, site, company)
- entity_id: UUID
- timestamp: timestamp
- efficiency: float
- cycle_time: integer
- bottleneck_status: boolean
- created_at: timestamp

## Relationships

1. Company (1) -> (n) Site
2. Site (1) -> (n) ValueStream
3. ValueStream (1) -> (n) Cell
4. Cell (1) -> (n) Operator
5. Cell (1) -> (n) ProductionCycle
6. Cell (1) -> (n) Downtime
7. Operator (1) -> (n) ProductionCycle
8. Operator (1) -> (n) Downtime

## Access Control Rules

### Company & Site Level
- Locked upon user registration
- Cannot be changed after initial setup
- Admin access required for configuration

### Value Stream & Cell Level
- Can be switched by authorized users
- Supervisors can manage configurations
- Operators can view assigned areas

### Operator Level
- Limited to assigned Cell and Value Stream
- Can log cycles and downtime
- Cannot modify configuration settings

## Efficiency Calculation Rules

1. Cell Efficiency:
   ```
   efficiency = (standard_cycle_time / actual_cycle_time) * 100
   ```

2. Value Stream Efficiency:
   ```
   efficiency = avg(cell_efficiencies)
   ```

3. Site Efficiency:
   ```
   efficiency = avg(value_stream_efficiencies)
   ```

4. Company Efficiency:
   ```
   efficiency = avg(site_efficiencies)
   ```

## Bottleneck Detection

1. Cell Level:
   - Compare actual_cycle_time against target_cycle_time
   - Flag if actual_cycle_time > target_cycle_time * 1.2

2. Value Stream Level:
   - Identify cell with highest average cycle time
   - Compare against value stream target efficiency

## Real-time Updates

- WebSocket events emitted for:
  1. Cycle completion
  2. Downtime logging
  3. Efficiency updates
  4. Bottleneck detection

## Background Processing

- BullMQ jobs for:
  1. Efficiency calculations
  2. Bottleneck analysis
  3. Report generation
  4. Historical data aggregation 